# Ask The Oracles — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Multi-LLM query interface. User types a question, all configured LLMs respond in parallel, then a Judge synthesizes all responses into a final recommendation.

## Stack
- React 18 + Vite
- Vanilla CSS (no Tailwind, no UI library)
- API SDKs: openai, @anthropic-ai/sdk, @google/generative-ai
- Mistral and Perplexity via fetch (REST)
- All keys via VITE_ env vars in .env

## File Structure
```
src/
  components/
    QueryBox.jsx         # Top input + Ask The Oracles button
    OracleCard.jsx       # Per-LLM card (logo, model picker, response, copy btn)
    OracleGrid.jsx       # Flex/grid layout for all oracle cards
    JudgePanel.jsx       # Synthesis panel that slides in between query and oracles
  hooks/
    useOracles.js        # Orchestrates parallel API calls, state mgmt
    useJudge.js          # Anthropic judge call
  utils/
    api.js               # All LLM API call functions
    models.js            # Model configs per provider
  App.jsx
  main.jsx
  index.css
```

## Coding Conventions
- Functional components only, hooks for all logic
- No class components
- CSS variables for all colors/spacing (defined in index.css :root)
- No inline styles except for dynamic/JS-driven values
- All API calls in utils/api.js only — no fetch/SDK calls in components
- Parallel API calls via Promise.allSettled (never sequential)
- Error states per-oracle, not global

## Key Behaviors
- "Ask The Oracles" triggers all enabled LLMs simultaneously
- Each oracle card animates in from the left, shows a skeleton loader
- Copy button appears only when that oracle's response is complete
- "Judge & Sync" button appears only after ALL oracles have resolved (success or error)
- Judge panel slides in above oracle grid, pushing it down
- Max page width: 1280px, centered

## Env Vars
All prefixed with VITE_ for Vite client exposure:
- VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY
- VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
- VITE_GROK_API_KEY
- VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY
- VITE_MISTRAL_API_KEY
- VITE_PERPLEXITY_API_KEY

## Do Not
- Do not use any CSS framework
- Do not use React Router (single page)
- Do not store responses in localStorage
- Do not make API calls server-side (all client-side for local dev)
- Do not use default exports for utils — named exports only
